# Example mappings.cfg for GamepadMidiController
# Lines starting with '#' are comments and ignored.
# Format:
#   button <BUTTON_NAME> <note|cc> <CHANNEL> <NUMBER> [VELOCITY]
#     - BUTTON_NAME: A, B, X, Y, LB, RB, BACK, START, GUIDE
#     - For "note" specify CHANNEL(1-16) NOTE_NUMBER(0-127) VELOCITY(0-127)
#     - For "cc" specify CHANNEL(1-16) CC_NUMBER(0-127)
#
#   axis <AXIS_NAME> cc <CHANNEL> <CC_NUMBER> <IN_MIN> <IN_MAX>
#     - AXIS_NAME: LEFT_STICK_X, LEFT_STICK_Y, RIGHT_STICK_X, RIGHT_STICK_Y, LEFT_TRIGGER, RIGHT_TRIGGER
#     - IN_MIN/IN_MAX define the input range mapping (usually -1.0 to 1.0 or 0.0 to 1.0)
#
# Examples:
# Send middle C (note 60) on channel 1 when A is pressed (velocity 100)
button A note 1 60 100

# Send CC 21 on channel 1 when B is pressed
button B cc 1 21

# Map left trigger to CC 70 on channel 2, input range 0.0..1.0
axis LEFT_TRIGGER cc 2 70 0.0 1.0

# Map left stick X/Y to CCs 10 and 11 on channel 2 with -1.0..1.0 input range
axis LEFT_STICK_X cc 2 10 -1.0 1.0
axis LEFT_STICK_Y cc 2 11 -1.0 1.0

# Notes:
# - If an axis is mapped (X or Y) the program sends per-axis CC messages.
# - If left/right sticks are not mapped, the program falls back to the original "chord" behavior.
# - Channels are 1-16. MIDI numbers and CC values must be 0-127.
